  "body": "# Tracking issue for [Kintsugi Milestones](https://hackmd.io/@tvanepps/amphora-milestones#Milestones)\r\n\r\n## [Milestones](https://notes.ethereum.org/@djrtwo/kintsugi-milestones#Milestones)\r\n- [x] M0: Implementation started\r\n- [x] M1: Implement latest spec - https://hackmd.io/@n0ble/kintsugi-spec#Execution-layer\r\n- [x] M2: 1-to-1 Interop ‚Äì One EL and one CL team pair off for basic interop\r\n- [x] M3: Many-to-Many Interop ‚Äì 2 or more EL and CL teams perform interop testing\r\n- [x] M4: Weekly devnet ‚Äì Weekly devnet for more in-depth testing\r\n- [x] M5: All-to-All persistent testnet ‚Äì All ready EL and CL teams create a long-lived devnet first week of december\r\n- [ ] M6: Kintsugiüçµ code released ‚Äì All clients release Kintsugiüçµ code for public consumption\r\n\r\n## Building and Running Besu in Interop Mode \r\n* clone/fetch the [latest merge branch](https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/tree/merge-branch)\r\n* merge consensus is gated by a flag `--Xmerge-support=true`\r\n* Besu will run/transition from whatever consensus mechanism is defined in the genesis config file at the specified terminalTotalDifficulty\r\n* to start besu in interop mining mode from the checked-out repo, e.g.:\r\n```bash\r\ngit clone --recursive https://github.com/hyperledger/besu\r\ngit checkout merge\r\n./gradlew --parallel installDist && build/install/besu/bin/besu --config-file=besu-config.toml\r\n```\r\n\r\n`besu-config.toml`\r\n```toml\r\ngenesis-file=\"genesis.json\"\r\ndata-path=\"besu-data\"\r\nnetwork-id=<TBD>\r\nrpc-http-enabled=true\r\nrpc-http-api=[\"ADMIN\",\"ETH\",\"NET\",\"DEBUG\",\"TXPOOL\",\"EXECUTION\"]\r\nhost-allowlist=[\"*\"]\r\nrpc-http-cors-origins=[\"*\"]\r\nrpc-http-port=8550\r\nXmerge-support=true\r\nlogging=\"DEBUG\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n* __PoW__ genesis config files require a consensus engine block.  Unlike geth besu does not default to ethash if there is no explicit consensus mechanism.  Besu requires the devnet genesis files to have an empty `ethash{}` entry in the config block for a PoW network.",
